The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
		 Wednesday, February 04, 2004  Sudhangshu Sekhar Dey Proprietor, Deys Publishing Yes. It would be a good idea to  take up the slogan of One visitor, one book. The crowd  at the Fair is rising every year, but there is no direct  relation between the footfall and the sales. Exemptions  may be made for members of a single family, or people who  have made a purchase on earlier days. Narayan Sanyal Writer No. Many of the pandal-hoppers  during the Pujas are not devotees. Does that stop them from  appreciating the images? People come to the fair to see  books and cull information. Our royalty cheques prove that  books are still selling. If all the visitors are not buying  books, it is our failing that we cannot write to satisfy  varied tastes
